# Object file for xAdventure

# Warning : The last line must be finished by a new line character

# Warning : For description, the max length of a line of text is
#   defined as a preprocessor macro called OBJ_MAX_LINE in load_object.h
#   but this limitation is avoid cause you can made multiline description
#   when a line finish with the '\' character, the parser will treat
#   the next line as a description continuation.

# Note : find percentage is express with exponent cause it seems
#   to be more error-less than floating point number. Please use 432e-2 for
#   4.32f. You may want to know that it is not a percent. It is treated
#   in get_random_object() function, implemented in object_list.c. Think
#   about this number as a fraction to the total find_percent of all
#   objects. The use should be : 
#   - 5.0 is an object we can easily find;
#   - 1.0 is a rare object
#   - under 0.1, The amout of find_percent is ridiculous from the total :)

# Each object is defined as
# alpha_id : An alphanumeric id, without spaces, unique and used in map
# english name
# french name
# english description
# french description
# weight in gramms
# find percentage as a float
# type value : Values depends on type (Should be the same in load_objects.h)

# Values of type are : 
# Type                   Value(s)
# 001 Food object        food raise value
# 002 Water object       water raise value

